                <summary>Colonel H. B. Davidson, commandant of the post at Staunton, has been
                    transferred, at his own request, to the field and assigned to duty in Tennessee.
                    Davidson has made many friends in Staunton and will be missed. However, he
                    wanted to return to active duty. Colonel J. Q. A. Nadenboush of the 2nd Virginia
                    Infantry will succeed him.</summary>
